OL,3,CInvestigations launched in crackdown
OL,4,Con unlicensed Botox products
OL,6,FDuring the summer several people in
OL,7,Fthe Durham and Darlington areas were
OL,8,Fsaid to have had to seek medical
OL,9,Ftreatment for suspected botulism,
OL,10,Fwhich is a rare and potentially life-
OL,11,Fthreatening condition which can cause
OL,12,Fparalysis.
OL,14,FBetween June 4 and August 6, there
OL,15,Fwere 41 confirmed cases of botulism
OL,16,Freported across the North East, East
OL,17,FMidlands, East of England, North West,
OL,18,Fand Yorkshire and Humber. Many people
OL,19,Fare reported to have been left
OL,20,F"seriously ill" as a result.
