OL,3,CInvestigations launched in crackdown
OL,4,Con unlicensed Botox products
OL,6,FThe MHRA's Criminal Enforcement Unit
OL,7,Freported that it has seen evidence of
OL,8,Fsome practitioners, who are often
OL,9,Funtrained, obtaining unlicensed
OL,10,Fbotulinum toxin products illegally.
OL,12,FInjections were then offered in
OL,13,F"unsafe, unregulated settings,"
OL,14,Fincluding bedrooms, kitchens, hair
OL,15,Fsalons and through mobile beauty
OL,16,Fservices.
OL,18,FIt said that people are often "lured
OL,19,Fin by adverts on social media
OL,20,Fpromising quick, cheap results".
